title: California Crime Rate Analysis
description: Analyzed California Crime Rate and Law Enforcement Data (2015) using Python and other libraries including NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, and Seaborn. Outcomes such as the most frequent crimes, most dangerous areas, impact of law enforcement rate on crime rates, and other factors affecting crime rate were outputted and visualized based on existing datasets.

title: Global Electric Vehicle Data Analysis
description: Led data analysis of the 2023 Global Electric Vehicle Dataset using Python, NumPy, Pandas, and Matplotlib to derive insights on EV market trends across key global economies, using data to uncover global renewable energy industry insights.

title: I'm Bored Chrome Extension
description: Designed and built a fun Chrome Extension using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript with 2,000+ users. A single click leads you to a randomized page to cure boredom. Integrated up to 50+ fun, interactive, odd, weird, and wacky pages.

title: AHAS Partshop's Order Management System
description: Designed and programmed AHAS Partshop’s order management system with searching, sorting, and object-oriented programming algorithms. Utilized HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap for the front-end programming of the system with PHP and MySQL for the back-end.
